# Admin User

Using this endpoints you can view, create and delete admin users.

## Admin Users [/api/admin/admin_users]

### Index [GET]
Lists Admin Users

Example:

```bash
curl https://railsskeleton.daliaresearch.com/api/admin/admin_users \
     -H 'Authorization: Dalia FAKE_ADMIN_TOKEN'
```

+ Response 200
  + Attributes (array[AdminUser])

### Show [GET /api/admin/admin_users/{admin_user_uuid}]
Displays Admin User data for given UUID

Example:

```bash
curl https://railsskeleton.daliaresearch.com/api/admin/admin_users/91fb9777-daa9-4b4e-94c9-1673b941875c \
     -H 'Authorization: Dalia FAKE_ADMIN_TOKEN'
```

+ Parameters
  + `admin_user_uuid`: `91fb9777-daa9-4b4e-94c9-1673b941875c` (string) UUID of Admin User

+ Response 200
  + Attributes (AdminUser)

### Create [POST]
Creates Admin User
Example:

```bash
curl -X POST \
  https://railsskeleton.daliaresearch.com/api/admin/admin_users \
  -H 'Authorization: Dalia FAKE_ADMIN_TOKEN' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  --data '{"admin_user":{"email":"joeadmin@daliaresearch.com","name":"Joe Admin","password":"p4sswORd!","password_confirmation":"p4sswORd!"}}'
```

+ Request (application/json)
  + Body

            {
              "admin_user": {
                "email": "joeadmin@daliaresearch.com",
                "name": "Joe Admin",
                "password": "p4sswORd!",
                "password_confirmation": "p4sswORd!"
              }
            }

+ Response 201

+ Response 422 (application/json; charset=utf-8)
  + Attributes (ResponseErrors)

